Class Description
AbstractFrame
An abstract class to denote the concept of a graphical window within which content can be displayed.
AddressBar
A class to represent an address bar in the browsr, as an extension of a AbstractFrame, in the UI layer.
BookmarksBar
A class to represent a graphical area that displays the currently saved bookmarks, along with providing the option of clicking on one of the bookmarks to navigate to the associated URL.

A class to represent a dialog screen that's displayed when the user wants to save a bookmark.

Browsr
A class to represent the UserInterface.Browsr window, with an AddressBar and a ContentFrame.
Browsr.Layout
An abstract class which represents the possible layouts of a Browsr object.
BrowsrLayout
An enumeration of the possible states of visible windows at this time in this Browsr.
ContentFrame
A class to represent frames containing content to be displayed in browsr, extended from AbstractFrame.
ContentSpan
A class to represent a superordinate, abstract object that represents the contents that are on a certain webpage.
ContentSpanBuilder
A class to handle the task of receiving tokens of BrowsrDocumentValidator and converting them to ContentSpan's.
Document
A class to represent an abstract document.
DocumentCell
A class extended from AbstractFrame to represent individual UI elements that need to be rendered.
DocumentCellDecorator
A class of decorators that decorate a visualization of a DocumentCell in browsr with a scroll bar.
DocumentKeeper
A class that keeps track of the documents associated to the windows in the UI-layer, as well as the ContentFrame that currently has focus.
DocumentListener
